Here are the latest results for the 2022 Pinellas County municipal elections. Seats are up for grabs in the cities and towns of Belleair Beach, Belleair Bluffs, Clearwater, Madeira Beach, Oldsmar, Redington Shores, St. Pete Beach and Tarpon Springs. In all but two races, the candidate with the most votes wins. Voters in Belleair Bluffs will elect the top two vote-getters in the three-way race for City Commission, and voters in Belleair Beach will elect the top three vote-getters in the six-way race for City Council. Charter amendments are on the ballot in Belleair, Madeira Beach, Oldsmar and Redington Beach. In Madeira Beach and Redington Beach, voters are weighing in on referendums. Polls close at 7 p.m. on Tuesday, March 15. Please use a modern browser to view the results.